00:03:59.780 --> 00:04:03.080
So this equation, so we have
to find all of the x's that

00:04:03.080 --> 00:04:10.280
satisfy, the first one right
here is the matrix 1, 3, 2, 6

00:04:10.280 --> 00:04:16.589
times x1, x2 is equal
to the zero vector.

00:04:16.589 --> 00:04:18.380
That's this equation
right there.

00:04:18.380 --> 00:04:20.240
We need to find all of the
solutions to that.

00:04:20.240 --> 00:04:21.790
And you might already
recognize it.

00:04:21.790 --> 00:04:25.540
All of the solutions to this,
all of the x's that satisfy

00:04:25.540 --> 00:04:27.750
this, is the null space
of this matrix.

00:04:27.750 --> 00:04:30.210
I just thought I'd point
that out on the side.

00:04:30.210 --> 00:04:32.530
Now, that's not the only one.

00:04:32.530 --> 00:04:34.270
We also have to solve
this guy over here.

00:04:34.270 --> 00:04:36.690
I'll do that in blue.

00:04:36.690 --> 00:04:40.080
So the preimage of S under
T is going to be all the

00:04:40.080 --> 00:04:48.280
solutions to this plus all of
the solutions to 1, 3, 2, 6

00:04:48.280 --> 00:04:54.300
times x1, x2 is equal to 1, 2.

00:04:54.300 --> 00:04:57.280
Now we can just solve this
with an augmented matrix.

00:04:57.280 --> 00:05:03.230
So my augmented matrix would
look like 1, 3, 2, 6, 0, 0.

00:05:03.230 --> 00:05:09.160
And here my augmented matrix
would be 1, 3, 2, 6, 1, 2.

00:05:09.160 --> 00:05:11.960
Let's put this in reduced
row echelon form.

00:05:11.960 --> 00:05:15.580
So let's replace our second row
with our second row minus

00:05:15.580 --> 00:05:17.880
2 times the first row.

00:05:17.880 --> 00:05:19.450
So what do we get?

00:05:19.450 --> 00:05:21.930
Our first row stays the same.

00:05:21.930 --> 00:05:24.960
1, 3, 0.

00:05:24.960 --> 00:05:27.110
Let me do them simultaneously.

00:05:27.110 --> 00:05:28.590
Let me solve these systems
in parallel.

00:05:28.590 --> 00:05:31.880
So my first system stays, first
row stays the same.

00:05:31.880 --> 00:05:33.710
1, 3, 1.

00:05:33.710 --> 00:05:36.490
And in both cases, because I
just want to get the left hand

00:05:36.490 --> 00:05:39.660
side of my augmented matrix into
reduced row echelon form,

00:05:39.660 --> 00:05:41.840
I can apply the same
row operation.

00:05:41.840 --> 00:05:44.680
So I'm replacing my second row
with 2 times my first row.

00:05:44.680 --> 00:05:48.040
So 2 minus 2 times 1 is 0.

00:05:48.040 --> 00:05:50.400
6 minus 2 times 3 is 0.

00:05:50.400 --> 00:05:54.650
And of course 0 minus
2 times 0 is 0.

00:05:54.650 --> 00:05:58.860
Here 2 minus 2 times 1 is 0.

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:01.420
6 minus 2 times 3 is 0.

00:06:01.420 --> 00:06:04.950
And 2 minus 2 times 1 is 0.

00:06:04.950 --> 00:06:07.080
So we get all these zeroes,
and we're actually done.

00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:10.100
We have both of these augmented
matrices in reduced

00:06:10.100 --> 00:06:11.420
